12.19.17  6:43 pm   I saw an interview with Dennis Rodman the other day. People are always giving him shit and making fun of him, but I respect what he's doing. It's better to have some positive dialogue with kim jong un, even if it's just about basketball, as opposed to no dialogue at all or only negative stuff.

     Also, I don't really know what to believe about kim or north korea. All the crazy bullshit we say about them could just be propaganda to make all the americans know who the 'bad guys' are. When 2 countries don't get along, I think it's common for both sides to make up lies and exaggerate to dehumanize the other country and make them seem evil and all that.
